		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://today.uic.edu?p=73028&#038;preview=true&#038;preview_id=73028</guid>
				<description><![CDATA[Dr. Frank González from the Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology [&#8230;]]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="pf-content">
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter"><a href="https://today.uic.edu/polycystic-ovary-syndrome-pcos-research-study"><img src="https://today.uic.edu/files/2019/08/DO-YOU-HAVE-PCOS-FLYER-V1_6x4-590x332.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-81849" srcset="https://today.uic.edu/files/2019/08/DO-YOU-HAVE-PCOS-FLYER-V1_6x4-590x332.jpg 590w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2019/08/DO-YOU-HAVE-PCOS-FLYER-V1_6x4-390x219.jpg 390w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2019/08/DO-YOU-HAVE-PCOS-FLYER-V1_6x4-768x432.jpg 768w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2019/08/DO-YOU-HAVE-PCOS-FLYER-V1_6x4-500x281.jpg 500w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2019/08/DO-YOU-HAVE-PCOS-FLYER-V1_6x4-1000x563.jpg 1000w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2019/08/DO-YOU-HAVE-PCOS-FLYER-V1_6x4-1320x743.jpg 1320w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2019/08/DO-YOU-HAVE-PCOS-FLYER-V1_6x4.jpg 1800w" sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px" /></a></figure></div>


<p>Dr. Frank González from the Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology at UIC is seeking women diagnosed with Polycystic Ovary Syndrome (PCOS) for a research study. The goal of this research study is to determine how treatment with a medication called Salsalate can improve the function of your ovaries, change your body’s insulin response to sugar (glucose), and reduce inflammation in your body triggered by certain components in the common diet.</p>
<p><strong>You may be able to participate if:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>You have been diagnosed with PCOS</li>
<li>You are healthy and aged 18-40</li>
<li>You currently have a BMI between 18-25 or 30-40</li>
<li>You have infrequent menstrual periods</li>
<li>You have excessive facial/body hair or acne</li>
<li>You are not pregnant</li>
<li>You do not take birth control pills or other sex hormones</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>For more information please contact the study coordinator:</strong><br>PCOS_study@uic.edu<br>(312) 996-6675</p>
<p>UIC IRB #2017-0476</p>
<p><strong>For more information, please contact:</strong><br>Frank Gonzalez</p>
<p>pcos_study@uic.edu</p>
<p></p>
